<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MCCARTY-COLUMN0812-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    More diversity please
 &HT;    By Mary McCarty
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   DAYTON, Texas _ When Al Gore introduced his new running mate
Tuesday _ Joseph Lieberman, America's first Jewish
vice-presidential candidate _ the mood in Nashville was jubilant.
The theme of the party: ``Isn't it great that we live in America,
where such a thing can happen?''
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, in the months and weeks leading up to the election,
as the two major parties moved inexorably to the nomination of yet
another daring combination of Four White Guys, I've found myself
asking a different question: ``This is America! Why can't we get
some semblance of diversity on the ticket?''
</P>
<P>
   So it's at once heartening that Lieberman is in the race and
disheartening that everyone is making such a big deal of it. That
what Lieberman describes simply as ``my faith; it's who I am'' is
being debated as a potential political liability.
</P>
<P>
   ve ahead with where we need to be in America.''
</P>
<P>
   The Gore/Lieberman ticket would say that's exactly what they're
doing. ``We're the American dream team,'' Lieberman exulted
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   His selection is a step in the right direction. Still, when
countries from Israel to Pakistan, from England to India have
elected women as leaders, it's hard to feel too exuberant about
America's record. When will women and blacks get serious
consideration on the ticket _ and not just for the No. 2 spot? How
many more decades, how many more elections will we have to wait?
</P>
<P>
   We have, for the first time in history, a Jewish vice
presidential candidate. Isn't it great that we live in America,
where such a thing can happen?
</P>
<P>
   Yes it is. But wouldn't it be even greater if we lived in an
America where such a thing happened so routinely that it barely
seemed worth noting?
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
