<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL;  PA Contract Awards By Jimmy Chuang States News Service
Washington, August 11 -- Elevator Company of America of Sewickley
won a $57,975 contract from the Department of Veterans Affairs in
Pittsburgh for maintenance, repair and rebuilding of equipment.
</P>
<P>
   Analytical Laboratory Services Inc. of Middletown won a $232,971
contract from the U.S. Environmental Protection Agency in
Philadelphia for professional, administrative and management
support services.
</P>
<P>
   Lockheed Martin Corp. of Philadelphia won a $63,295 contract
from the U.S. Naval Air Systems Command in Patuxent River, Md., for
guided missiles.
</P>
<P>
   York International Corp. of York won a $53,770 contract from the
U.S. Navy in Mechanicsburg for refrigeration, air condition and air
circulating equipment.
</P>
<P>
   United Dominion Industries Inc. of West Mifflin won a $188,294
contract from the U.S. Navy in Mechanicsburg for furnace, steam
plant, drying equipment and nuclear reactors.
</P>
<P>
   General Aviation Manufacturing Inc. of Huntingdon Valley won a
$82,477 contract from the Defense Industrial Supply Center in
Philadelphia for hardware and abrasives.
</P>
<P>
   SPS Technologies Inc. of Jenkintown won a $98,400 contract from
the Defense Industrial Supply Center in Philadelphia for hardware
and abrasives.
</P>
<P>
   Chant Engineering Co. Inc. of New Britain won a $919,980
contract from the U.S. Army Corps of Engineers in Pittsburgh for
electrical and electronic equipment components.
</P>
<P>
   Wheeler Brothers Inc. of Somerset won a $133,626 contract from
the Defense General Supply Center in Richmond, Va., for electric
wire and power and distribution equipment.
</P>
<P>
   Draeger Safety Inc. of Pittsburgh won a $60,634 contract from
the Defense General Supply Center in Richmond, Va., for instruments
and laboratory equipment.
</P>
<P>
   Olympus Building Services Inc. of Doylestown won a $4 million
contract from the General Services Administration in Denver, Colo.,
for utilities and housekeeping services.
</P>
<P>
   Fry Communications Inc. of Mechanicsburg won a $948,375 contract
from the U.S. Government Printing Office in Washington for
photographic, mapping, printing and publication services.
</P>
<P>
   Vertech International Inc. of Warminster won a $322,470 contract
from the Defense Supply Center in Columbus, Ohio, for aircraft
launching, landing and ground handling equipment.
</P>
<P>
   -30-
</P>
</TEXT>
