<P>
   DON'T UNDERESTIMATE AOL LATIN AMERICA, by David Kurapka
</P>
<P>
   The lackluster reception of investors to the initial public
offering AOL Latin America (AOLA on the Nasdaq) speaks less about
America Online and its strategy in the region then about interest
in Latin American Internet plays in general.
</P>
<P>
   AOL Latin America may never be able to dominate the region the
way its parent company has dominated the U.S. Of course, that does
not mean that their regional hopes will come to naught, just that
they are coming to the party while everyone is still nursing a
hangover. And sooner or later the party will start again.
</P>
