<P>
   CLEANING-CHIC (Undated) _ Cleaning has come out of the broom
closet. A new home magazine, Dwell, debuts this month with a cover
line that reads: ``The Most Beautiful Vacuum Cleaners on Earth.''
Cleaning has gone all high-tech, and looks gender-neutral. You
might call it indoor gardening. By Penelope Green.
</P>
<P>
   DENEUVE-DIAMONDS (New York) _ It is here on 47th Street that an
extraordinary percentage of all the gem diamonds on the world
market are faceted, bought and sold; that lobby clocks are set to
times in the diamond capitals of the world (New York, London,
Antwerp); that Hasidic merchants bustle around carrying millions of
dollars of gems in cloth wallets beneath their trousers; that
security is so tight even Catherine Deneuve is stopped for
identification.
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
</P>
<P>
   THONG-POPULARITY (Undated) _ Once the province solely of the
taut-thighed pubescent underwear models and Rio de Janerio beach
bunnies, thongs, it seems have quietly made it into the mainstream.
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
</P>
<P>
   RAZOR-SCOOTERS (Undated) _ Since arriving from Hong Kong at
Christmas, the chrome Razor scooters, which go for about $100 a
pop, have been selling out at both Toys ``R'' Us and the Sharper
Image, appealing equally to superannuated kids and to the regular
kind. By John Leland.
</P>
<P>
   GARDEN-COLUMN (Undated) _ Are you one of those poor fools who
mows the lawn on a hill so steep you have to pull the mower back up
on a rope? And then your back goes out and you have to be hauled
off on a stretcher? That hill needs a ground cover. The same
applies if you are bashing into your trees with that mower. Stop,
unless you want to kill them. Plant a ground cover from the tree's
trunk clear to its drip line. Or even farther, if you would like a
sustainable, low-maintenance landscape. By Anne Raver.
</P>
