 &HT;    CoxNet Cox News Service Sports budget FOR Saturday, August 12,
2000
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   For questions, please call 404-526-5456
</P>
<P>
   FBN-SAPP _ Warren Sapp went silent. Honest. Sapp was talking
away, answering question after question, talking about how he loves
Miami - ``the fans, the sun, the women ... greatest city in the
world'' - when a reporter managed to plug the Hoover Dam of NFL
mouths with a mere two syllables. Todd Wade. (Palm Post Beach
Post). 22.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-HERSCHEL _ SOUTH BEND, Ind. _ Report on Herschel Walker's
enshrinement ceremony at the College Football Hall of Fame in South
Bend, Ind. (Schlabach, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 12.
</P>
<P>
   BOXING
</P>
<P>
   BOX-HOLYFIELD-ADVANCE _ As he approaches his 38th birthday,
Evander Holyfield is constantly faced with this question - how much
longer does he intend to fight? Holyfield wants to become the
undisputed heavyweight champion for the fourth time and he takes
the next step toward that goal Saturday as he faces John Ruiz for
the vacant WBC title. If he defeats Ruiz as expected, he could put
himself in position for another shot at the undisputed title. But
that fight might not occur until next year when he's approaching
39. (Tierney, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 25.
</P>
<P>
   AUTO RACING
</P>
<P>
   CAR-NASCAR-POLE _ WATKINS GLEN, N.Y. _ Report on the run for the
pole at Watkins Glen. ( Levine, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 14.
</P>
