<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   CANADA-SPECIES (Montreal) _ From giant American bullfrogs
marauding through the mud ponds of British Columbia to a proposal
to eradicate fish in a pristine lake high in the Rockies, it's
adding up to an ugly summer for aquatic species across Canada.
Alien species are displacing native ones. By Colin Nickerson. 1200
words.
</P>
<P>
   BRITAIN-BOY-CRITIC (London) _ A huge flap over disparaging
