<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   CANADA-SPECIES (Montreal) _ From giant American bullfrogs
marauding through the mud ponds of British Columbia to a proposal
to eradicate fish in a pristine lake high in the Rockies, it's
adding up to an ugly summer for aquatic species across Canada.
Alien species are displacing native ones. By Colin Nickerson. 1200
words.
</P>
<P>
   BRITAIN-BOY-CRITIC (London) _ A huge flap over disparaging
remarks by 15-year-old daughter of the US ambassador about British
boys takes a new turn as the ambassador says she never said they
``suck.'' By Kevin Cullen. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-MISSILES (Moscow) _ Amid warnings that much of Russia's
once-vaunted military is rusting away for lack of money, Vladimir
Putin and top generals debate whether to radically reorganize the
way its strategic missile force is run. By Brian Whitmore. 750
words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; POLITICS (p) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   CAMPAIGN-BUSH (Portland, Ore.) _ Confronting an issue he rarely
mentions by name, George W. Bush challenges his Democratic rival to
condemn President Clinton for his past behavior, saying Vice
President Al Gore ``ought to speak out'' on the impeachment scandal
if he is truly bothered by it. By Anne E. Kornblut. 1200 words.
</P>
<P>
   DEMS-MONEY (Washington) _ Like the Republicans, the Democrats
are taking advantage of federal campaign laws to use corporate
donations not only for their convention, but also for party
gatherings from Long Beach to Hollywood. By Glen Johnson. 1500
words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   EGYPTAIR-DOCUMENTS (Undated) _ Federal safety panel releases
more than 1,600 pages of documents related to the crash of Egyptair
990 off the New England coast. While the NTSB does not make any
conclusions about a crash cause, the documents contain interesting
new information. By Matthew Brelis. 1100 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   EXITSOURCE-SERVICES (Undated) _ Epitomizing how the wireless
Internet market is growing more in specific services rather than
Web-surfing from your phone, eXitsource is offering information
about services available at 20,000 US highway exits. With a few
clicks you can find out every McDonald's, hospital or hotel for the
next 100 miles. By Peter J. Howe. 1100 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SPORTS (s) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   BOX-RUIZ-COMMENT (Las Vegas) _ There is only one question on the
minds of everyone who has ever known John Ruiz. Can he do it? By
Ron Borges. 1900 words; includes Holyfield career text table.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; The Boston Globe &LR;  &QC;
