<P>
   FIRES-POLICY _ Have all the fires on national forests and other
public lands this summer forced officials to re-examine their fire
management policies in western Colorado? (Grand Junction Daily
Sentinel). 25. WITH PHOTO.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   FIRES-ARTIFACTS _ MESA VERDE, COLO. _ Story on how National Park
Service officials are protecting and handling all the archealogical
sites and artifacts that have been uncoverered by all the fires
this summer. (Grand Junction Daily Sentinel). 25-30. WITH PHOTO.
</P>
<P>
   BOB-DIARY _ The Bob Graham Diary. The saga of a journal and one
man's undoing. Word has it, Sen. Graham missed the VP nomination
because of eccentric note-taking habits. What's behind the call to
scrawl? WITH PHOTOS (Crowley, Palm Beach Post).
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   BOB-TIME_ A page from graham's diary. (Palm Beach Post)
</P>
<P>
   TRAFICANT-RENO _ Ohio Congressman James Traficant has long used
his mouth as a weapon of destruction, but rarely has his vitriol
been this personal. On a Fox News national news program Wednesday
Traficant levied a variety of sordid allegations against Attorney
General Janet Reno _ from mafia-supplied call girls to substance
abuse _ claiming secret affidavits that he refused to release.
Reno, in an unusually strong reaction, said people in public office
have to endure all sorts of nasty comments, but these are some of
the most nasty, unsubstantiated comments she has ever heard.
Traficant himself has said he is about to be indicted on federal
charges, raising questions about the real reason for his public
broadside against the Justice Department. (Montgomery, Cox News
Service). 30 inches. WILL MOVE SATURDAY.
</P>
<P>
   CAMILLA-VICTIMS _ Six months after a tornado struck Camilla,
many victims are back on their feet and rebuilding their homes. The
reason for the rebound, victims say, is a rich neighborhood spirit
and the overwhelming kindness of strangers. (Osinski, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   CVN-GORE _ LOS ANGELES _ After months of campaigning hard before
an inattentive public, Al Gore will find his spotlight this week at
the podium of the
</P>
<P>
   Democratic National Convention. Here's what he and his party
must accomplish this week. (Shepard, Cox News Service). Moving
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   WAN: Atlanta, National, Politics
</P>
<P>
   CVN-CLINTON _ WASHINGTON _ President Clinton takes the stage
Monday at the Democratic National Convention with two distinct _
but conflicting _ goals. One
</P>
<P>
   is to celebrate his own presidency's eight years of peace and
prosperity and to claim a place in history on his own terms. The
other is proclaim Al Gore as the
</P>
<P>
   co-author and rightful heir to the administration's successful
policies while minimizing his ties to its scandals. (Deans, Cox
News Service).
</P>
<P>
   Moving Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   WAN: Atlanta, National, Politics
</P>
