<P>
   COXNET LIFESTYLES 0812: SHOPPING TIME AGAIN: It's time for
pencils. It's time for books. It's time for sales clerks' dirty
looks. The back-to-school shopping season is here. As always, it's
a chore that requires preparation, patience and perseverance. Here
are some practical tips for surviving the back-to-school challenge.
(Harris, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) Art includes a 4-column
color illustration of a woman shopping in acrowded store.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: SPECIAL TREATS BOX -- Few parents indulge their kids with
all the clothes and gadgets they want for school, but one or two
treats can help make the semester more exiting. Here are some
ideas. Art includes a 1-column color photo of wristbands and a
6-pica color photo of a Powerpuff Girl.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: COOL IN SCHOOL -- The carefree days of vacation are
quickly giving way to the grueling days of school. In the likely
event your anxious offspring think the situation is simply too grim
to bear, show them these cool tools for school. (Morrow, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) Art includes a 2-column color photo of a
