   SCIENCE/MEDICINE
</P>
<P>
   COXNET SCIHEALTH PAGE
</P>
<P>
   EDs: This is the CoxNet SCIHEALTH page for the current week.
This layout is now available.
</P>
<P>
   CoxNet HEALTHY LIVING 0812: DRINK WATER _ Most people need to
drink more than eight glasses of water a day. The reasons we need
water are many. After oxygen, water is the human body's most
important need. Our bodies consist largely of water, and water
plays a role in nearly every major bodily function. (Lore, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) Art includes a 5-column color photo
illustration of a person pouring eight glasses of water and a
2-column color photo of a woman pouring water into a glass from a
large jug.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   AT-A-GLANCE BOXES _ Boxes showing foods that help hydrate, ways
to test for the purity of tap water and facts about water filters.
(Lore, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   STROKES DANGER _ Relatively few Americans understand what
strokes are, or know enough about them to recognize their symptoms,
even though strokes affect more than 600,000 Americans every year.
(McKenna, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   PREGNANT TEENS _ Nationwide, the rate of teenage pregnancies is
dropping, even as more youths are becoming sexually active and at
younger ages. (McLachlin, Palm Beach Post)
</P>
<P>
   FLAVORED MEDICINE _ Sour apple, cinnamon, root beer or mint
chocolate _ choose a flavor. Parents can take a vacation from
tantrums and screeching cries since pharmacist-technician Kenneth
Kramm invented Flavorx _ 42 flavors to cover the bitter taste of
some prescribed and over-the-counter liquid medicine. (Villalobos,
Dayton Daily News) Art includes a 2-column color photo of a
pharmacist mixing medication and a 6-pica color illustration of a
computer.
</P>
