   JAPAN-RATES (Tokyo) _ The Bank of Japan ended its policy of zero
interest rates on Friday, defying government calls for a delay in a
rate increase in what has been the biggest public fight over
Japanese economic policy this century. After 17 months of near-zero
rates, the central bank raises its target for overnight lending to
0.25 percent _ the first rate increase in a decade. By Calvin Sims.
