   EGYPTAIR-CRASH (Washington) _ Government safety investigators
offer new evidence that the crash of Egyptair 990 into the Atlantic
Ocean last October was the deliberate act of a relief co-pilot, and
that there was no mechanical problem with the plane. After a
10-month investigation that has strained relations between the
United States and Egypt, the NTSB released nearly 1,700 pages of
documents, including reports from the FBI showing that the co-pilot
had been accused of a variety of sexual improprieties at a New York
City hotel during visits there in the year before the crash. By
