times of soaring prosperity, voters do not defeat the presidential
candidate of the party in power. If that tradition prevails in
November, Al Gore will win. But another rule, which will help
George W. Bush, is that people favor a return to the White House of
the party that has been out of power for a while. By ROBERT E.
THOMPSON. (Filed Wednesday.)
</P>
