   TECHNO-FORUM (Los Angeles) _ Several of Southern California's
leading businessmen and politicians participated Friday in an
economic forum on the future of techology in Los Angeles. By Chris
Sieroty.
</P>
<P>
   BRACELET (Northridge, Calif.) _ Gina Eckstein and Ivette Helfend
have been in business together since the were children. Growing up
in Mexico City, the sisters got in trouble for reselling the
chocolate they'd persuaded their mother to buy for them. Now
they've taken a $2,000 investment and turned it into a business
they expect to gross $200,000 by the end of the year. By Pam Park.
</P>
