<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MIDWAY-IFYOUGO13-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Midway if you go
 &HT;    Eds: Embargoed for Sunday, Aug. 13.
 &HT;    By Howard Pousner
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QR;  Getting there: Fly Delta Air Lines to Honolulu for $883 round
trip (Monday-Wednesday departures, Tuesday-Thursday returns), with
a 21-day advance purchase. (Fare rises to $995 Dec. 15.) From
Honolulu, Aloha Airlines offers weekly flights to Midway at 4 p.m.
Saturdays (returns, 7:17 p.m. Saturdays), $496 round trip (plus
applicable fees and taxes).
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Lodging and food: Prices range from $112 per person (single
room, shared bath) to $195 per person (three-room suite, private
bath), based on double occupancy. Prices include three meals daily
at your choice of the Clipper House or in the galley.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Information and reservations: Midway Phoenix Corp.,
1-888-643-9291,www.midwayisland.com.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  All-inclusive deal: Midway Phoenix Corp. is offering a special
package including round-trip air service from Atlanta to Midway on
Northwest and Aloha airlines, two nights' lodging at a first-class
Honolulu hotel, rental car for two days and airport-hotel
transfers. On Midway, the package includes seven nights' lodging
and three meals daily at the Clipper House or in the galley. Starts
at $2,999 per person, based on double occupancy (subject to
availability). Contact Sprayberry Travel, 770-977-0783 or
</P>
<P>
   1-888-299-8747.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Extras: golf carts, $30 a day; bicycles, $5 a day; cell
phones, $5 a day plus long-distance charges. Midway Phoenix offers
small-group, half-day naturalist tours for $20 per person. Fish and
Wildlife offers a variety of shorter nature and history tours and
videos and slide shows (free) throughout the week, including a boat
trip to Eastern Island, a former military site that has been
cleared and turned into bird habitat.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Fishing, scuba diving: Several packages are offered. Call
Destination: Midway, 1-888-244-8582; www.fishdive.com.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Volunteering on Midway: From November through July, Oceanic
Society Expeditions organizes nine-day seabird field research
projects. The $1,682 fee includes round-trip airfare from Honolulu,
room and board. Also offered: nine-day spinner dolphin research
projects, March-October; and nine-day Midway natural history
package tours. 1-800-326-7491, www.oceanic-society.org.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
