<HEADLINE>
CONGRESSWOMAN MOVES EVENT OUT OF PLAYBOY MANSION  

</HEADLINE>
   c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service  
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ Yielding to pressure from Vice President Al Gore
and other Democratic Party leaders, Rep. Loretta Sanchez agreed
Friday night to move a Hispanic fund-raising event from the Playboy
Mansion to Universal Studios.
</P>
<P>
   Sanchez, D-Calif., had been removed from the speaker's list at
the Democratic National Convention and faced further punishment
from the party's leadership after she refused to move the event,
which is to raise money to bring out the Hispanic vote.
</P>
<P>
   Her speaking engagement and her position as Democratic party
co-chairwoman were secured by her action Friday night, party
leaders said.
</P>
<P>
   ``To continue to dwell on where our event is held, and whether
my role as a DNC officer conflicts with my role at a party for a
good cause, frankly makes no sense,'' Sanchez said in a statement.
``The only real party I am interested in is a party that represents
real people, with real needs. That party is the Democratic Party.''
</P>
</TEXT>
